From: Steve French <sfrench@us.ibm.com>
Subject: [CIFS] remove unused list, add new cifs sock list to prepare
         for mount/umount fix
Patch-mainline: v2.6.28-rc3
References: https://bugzilla.samba.org/show_bug.cgi?id=5720
    
Also adds two lines missing from the previous patch (for the need
reconnect flag in the /proc/fs/cifs/DebugData handling)
    
The new global_cifs_sock_list is added, and initialized in init_cifs
but not used yet. Jeff Layton will be adding code in to use that and to
remove the GlobalTcon and GlobalSMBSession lists.
    
